thread.title: Power Still Out for Thousands in New York, New Jersey

author: Kate King
title: Power Still Out for Thousands in New York, New Jersey
text:
Thousands remained without power across New York and New Jersey Monday, three days after a powerful norâ€™easter slammed the East Coast and as the region gears up for another winter storm.
More than 60,000 people in Westchester County and 65,000 people in New Jersey were still without power as of midday Monday. Some school districts were closed as officials worked to remove fallen trees and direct traffic at intersections without working traffic signals.
